    {
        "content": "<p>It looks like we are talking about  <code>ARCH=arm64</code> and kernel v6.8.12. When was RUST aarch64 support merged?</p>",
        "id": 462762663,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1723805905
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>v6.9</p>",
        "id": 462763583,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1723806301
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/commit/?id=724a75ac9542f\">arm64: rust: Enable Rust support for AArch64</a> was merged with v6.9-rc1. So v6.8.12 is too old for Rust on arm64. You either need to switch to kernel &gt;=v6.9 or cherry pick the given patch to your v6.8 tree.</p>",
        "id": 462763597,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1723806306
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So it's missing from docs? Had no idea about 6.9</p>",
        "id": 462793352,
        "sender_full_name": "Nikolai Shv",
        "timestamp": 1723816678
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>So it's missing from docs?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I am not sure what you mean -- it is there in the docs (<a href=\"https://docs.kernel.org/rust/arch-support.html\">https://docs.kernel.org/rust/arch-support.html</a>).</p>\n<p>Which docs are you looking at?</p>",
        "id": 462794895,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1723817224
    },
